<h1> <img src="fightingmanagedcare.gif" alt="Fighting Managed Care"
 height="60" width="486"></h1>
</center>
<center><!-------Begin Copy Here-------><a
 href="http://www.goldenwebawards.com"><img src="webaward.jpg"
 border="0" height="120" width="88"></a><!-------End Copy Here------->
<p><a href="http://www.goldenwebawards.com"><img src="webaward2001f.gif"
 border="0" height="139" width="101"></a><img src="DECORATE3.jpg"
 alt="Molly Award" border="0" height="150" hspace="10" width="125">
<a href="http://members.atlantic.net/%7Ebdarl/index.html"><img
 src="cmaward_s.gif" alt="Critical Mass Award" border="0" height="100"
 width="83"></a><a href="http://www.high-density.com/"><img
 src="hawk50trans.gif" alt="Hawck Award" border="0" height="154"
 hspace="8" width="109">
</a> </p>
<p><b><font color="#ff0000">WE, HEALTH CARE PROFESSIONALS </font>CAN
AND MUST
HAVE A VOICE!</b> </p>
<p>We simply like to treat people regardless of who they are, where
they come
from, and who pays for it. We do it fee for service or with third party
payers.
Besides looking for our interests, we have another and more
important&nbsp;
responsibility: </p>
<p><b><i><font color="#ff0000">WE MUST WORK FOR A HEALTH CARE SYSTEM
THAT&nbsp; RESPONDS TO OUR PATIENTS' NEEDS!</font></i></b>. </p>
<p>It is unbelievable how we, mental health professionals, have been
-so far-
unable to organize ourselves to <font color="#ff0000">defend</font>
our professions
and our patients from the so called "market forces" of greedy health
corporations..
Click <a href="http://pw2.netcom.com/%7Emvp1/mcoproviders.htm">HERE </a>for
my presentation at the <a href="http://www.psych.org">American
Psychiatric Association</a> Meeting in Toronto in August 1998, where I
addressed this issue. I am glad to say that finally the American
Medical Association is proposing
that we physicians should get together as an Union to stand up for ours
and
our patients' rights. We must form a huge union of health care workers,
that
is, front line professionals who treat patients, to face the enormous
and
perverse threat of Health Corporations/HMOs/Managed Care. </p>
<p><i><u><font color="#cc0000">To discuss more health care go to this
newsgroup: <a href="http://www.deja.com">talk.politics.medicine</a></font></u></i>
</p>
