<p><b><font color="#ff0000">Links</font></b> <br>
Here are some links with organizations and groups that also want a
better
health care system for Americans. They may have different views on how
the
system should work in order to offer affordable, quality and universal
access
to all Americans. But they are united in at least one point: HMOs and
Managed
Care are not good health professionals and their patients! <br>
<img src="newflip.gif" alt="New" border="0" height="25" width="60">
<font color="#3333ff"><a
 href="http://www.geocities.com/RainForest/Canopy/5322/HMOconspiracy.html">Damaged
care, damaged caregiver<br>
Look a the sharks!</a></font> <br>
<a href="http://www.harp.org">Health Administration Responsibility
Project</a> <br>
<font color="#3333ff"><a href="http://www.deathbyhmo.com">Death by a HMO</a></font>
<br>
<b><a href="http://www.ccemhc.org">California Coalition for Ethical
Mental
Health Care</a></b> <br>
<b><i><font color="#3333ff"><a href="http://mentalhealth.about.com">Good
Mental
Health Information!</a></font></i></b> &nbsp; <br>
<a href="http://www.cchcc.org">Problems with your HMO or Insurance?
California
Consumer Health Care Council.</a> <br>
<font color="#cc0000"><a href="http://www.nomanagedcare.org">National
Coalition
of Mental Health Professionals &amp;Consumers</a></font> <br>
<a href="http://www.druglibrary.org/schaffer/asap">American Society for
Action
on Pain (ASAP)</a> <br>
<a href="http://nightingalenet.net">Here come the Nurses!</a> <br>
<a href="http://www.pnhp.org">Physicians for a National Health Program</a>
<br>
<u><a href="http://www.consumerwatchdog.org">Consumer Watchdog
Organization</a></u> <br>
<u><a href="http://www.florenceproject.org">Florence Project</a></u> <br>
<u><a href="http://www.uhcan.org">Uhcan</a></u> <br>
</p>
<p><img src="usflag.jpg" alt="USFlag" border="0" height="29" width="48">
<br>
<b><a href="http://thomas.loc.gov/cgi-bin/query/z?c105:h.r.1200:">A
SINGLE
PAYER IN THE US!</a></b> <br>
Did you all know that there is a proposition in <br>
the US Congress for a Single Payer Health Care? <br>
Rep. McDermott, a psychiatrist, is the author. <br>
</p>
<hr width="100%">If we, <i><font color="#ff0000">health care clinicians</font>,
</i>get together we will have a say about the conditions under which we
will
practice our noble professions. The problem has always been... <i><font
 color="#ff0000">how can we do it</font>? </i>Although we belong to
different
disciplines we must find a way to work together because we are the ones
on
the front lines, treating people. <br>
<b><font color="#ff0000">WE CARE!</font></b> <br>
<hr width="100%">HMOs and Managed Care For Profits are dismantling the
American
health care system. In Mental Health this has become a <font
 color="#ff0000">public calamity</font>. <br>
<b><font color="#ff0000">WHY?</font></b> <br>
<b><i><font color="#cc0000">Because for them, less care means more
profits!</font></i></b> <br>
<b><i><font color="#cc0000">They have created a carve out of mental
health
services separated from the rest of medicine. This carve outs are then
given
to Behavioral Managed Care Corporations For Profits that are making it
impossible
for mental patients to have proper treatments in America!</font></i></b>
<br>
